Abstract: Grasp learning is a pivotal area in robotics and machine learning, focusing on the development of models and methods for effective object manipulation. This research delves into the latest advancements in grasp learning, exploring various machine learning techniques that enhance robotic grasping capabilities. By analyzing performance metrics across different models, the study identifies key factors that contribute to successful grasp execution. The findings aim to provide a comprehensive understanding of the current state of grasp learning, offering insights into future directions for improving manipulation tasks in robotics through innovative machine learning approaches.
